# artix
install

**Artix Linux installer — a fork of [`archinstall`](https://github.com/archlinux/archinstall) adapted for Artix's init-agnostic package ecosystem.**

Same guided TUI. Same automation philosophy. All four Artix init systems.

---

## Quick start (Artix live ISO)

```bash
pacman -Sy python git --noconfirm
git clone https://github.com/your-org/artixinstall
cd artixinstall
pip install archinstall --break-system-packages
python -m artixinstall
```

The guided installer will present one additional menu item — **"Init system"** — between
Locales and Disk configuration. Everything else is identical to the archinstall you know.

---

## Supported init systems

| Init | Status | Service mechanism |
|------|--------|-------------------|
| **OpenRC** | ✅ Stable | `rc-update add/del` |
| **runit** | ✅ Stable | sv symlinks in `/etc/runit/runsvdir/current/` |
| **s6** | ⚠ Experimental | `contents.d` touch files (compiled at first boot) |
| **dinit** | ⚠ Experimental | symlinks in `/etc/dinit.d/boot.d/` |

---

## What artixinstall changes versus upstream archinstall

| Upstream behaviour | artixinstall behaviour |
|---|---|
| `systemctl --root enable <svc>` | `rc-update add` / sv symlink / contents.d / boot.d symlink |
| `systemd-timesyncd` | `openntpd` (all inits) |
| `fstrim.timer` | `/etc/cron.weekly/fstrim` shell script |
| systemd-networkd `.network` files | NetworkManager keyfiles |
| systemd-resolved symlink in `/etc/resolv.conf` | static resolv.conf with sane defaults |
| mkinitcpio hooks: `systemd sd-vconsole` | `udev keymap consolefont` |
| systemd-boot supported | **Blocked** — use GRUB |
| Arch repos `[core] [extra] [community]` | Artix repos `[system] [world] [galaxy]` (first) |
| packages like `networkmanager` | `networkmanager` + `networkmanager-<init>` |
| `systemd` in base packages | `elogind` + init-meta package |

---

## Architecture in one paragraph

artixinstall vendors upstream archinstall as a Python dependency and
**subclasses `Installer` in exactly 9 method overrides**. All init-specific
behaviour goes through an `InitBackend` abstract class with four concrete
implementations. The package mapping registry resolves every Arch package
name to its Artix equivalent (or `None` if it must be dropped). The guided
script is ~95% identical to upstream.

---

## Running the tests

```bash
python -m pytest tests/ -v
# 99 passed in 0.41s — no root, no live ISO, no chroot required
```

